<paragraph blockId="6.[151,452,153,180]" box="[151,452,153,180]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,452,153,180]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,452,153,180]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hood" authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1924" box="[238,452,153,180]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Stictothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,377,153,180]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Stictothrips</emphasis>
Hood
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,225,468]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
Currently this genus comprises five fungus-feeding species (
<bibRefCitation accessDate="2019-05-01" author="ThripsWiki" box="[821,1015,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" publicationUrl="http://thrips.info/wiki/" refId="ref7542" refString="ThripsWiki (2019) providing information on the World's thrips. Available from: http: // thrips. info / wiki / (accessed 1 May 2019)" title="providing information on the World's thrips" type="url" year="2019">ThripsWiki 2019</bibRefCitation>
) that have been described from several different parts of the world. The 
<typeStatus box="[540,588,262,288]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hood" authorityName="Hood" box="[689,904,261,288]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Stictothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[689,831,261,288]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">S. maculatus</emphasis>
Hood
</taxonomicName>
, is known from various parts of North America, with both sexes fully winged (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoddle" box="[502,725,297,323]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hoddle" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" refId="ref6313" refString="Hoddle, M., Mound, L. A. &amp; Paris, D. (2019) Thysanoptera Californica. An identification and information system to thrips in California. Available from: https: // keys. lucidcentral. org / keys / v 3 / thrips _ of _ california _ 2019 / (accessed 10 July 2019)" type="url" year="2019">
Hoddle 
<emphasis box="[596,655,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1925" box="[746,842,298,324]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Stictothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="faurei">
<emphasis box="[746,842,298,324]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">S. faurei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1086,1231,297,323]" name="South Africa" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and subsequently recorded (as 
<taxonomicName box="[295,427,333,360]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Stictothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis box="[295,427,333,360]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">S. fimbriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from 
<collectingCountry box="[504,562,333,359]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti" box="[576,776,333,360]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Bhatti" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref5849" refString="Bhatti, J., Alavi, J., Zur Strassen, R. &amp; Telmadarraiy, Z. J. T. (2009) Thysanoptera in Iran 1938 - 2007. An Overview. Part 1. Thrips, 7, 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="2009">
Bhatti 
<emphasis box="[653,702,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
); moreover 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheraghian" box="[909,1120,333,360]" firstAuthor="Cheraghian" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" refId="ref5897" refString="Cheraghian, A. (1996) A faunistic study of Thysanoptera in Ahwaz region. M. Sc. thesis, Shahid Chamran University, Ahwaz, Iran, 118 pp. (in Persian)." type="book" year="1996">Cheraghian (1996)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species in low density from 
<taxonomicName box="[303,505,369,395]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis box="[303,505,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Ficus bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[543,770,369,395]" country="Iran" name="Khuzestan" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Khuzestan province</collectingRegion>
, south of 
<collectingCountry box="[882,931,370,396]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Iran</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1932" box="[942,1104,369,396]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Stictothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leopardinus">
<emphasis box="[942,956,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[971,1104,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">leopardinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,406,432]" name="Egypt" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Egypt</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Priesner" box="[231,390,405,432]" firstAuthor="Priesner" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" pagination="1 - 549" refId="ref7458" refString="Priesner, H. (1965) A monograph of the Thysanoptera of the Egyptian deserts. Publications de la Institut Desert Egypte 13, 1 - 549." type="journal article" year="1965">Priesner 1965</bibRefCitation>
); and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mound &amp; Tree" authorityYear="2015" box="[455,572,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Stictothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aoristus">
<emphasis box="[455,572,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">S. aoristus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mound &amp; Tree" authorityYear="2015" box="[624,743,405,432]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Stictothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="namadji">
<emphasis box="[624,743,405,432]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">S. namadji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described from 
<collectingCountry box="[979,1082,405,431]" name="Australia" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mound &amp; Tree" box="[1095,1327,405,432]" firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="6" pageNumber="563" pagination="325 - 341" refId="ref7235" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Tree, D. J. (2015) Fungus-feeding Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripinae of the Idiothrips genus-group in Australia, with nine new species. Zootaxa, 4034 (2), 325 - 341. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4034.2.5" type="journal article" year="2015">Mound &amp; Tree 2015</bibRefCitation>
). To these five species, the following new species is described here from 
<collectingCountry box="[852,901,442,468]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
